---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Us"
  description="Meet the team at Morning Star Neuropathy & Pain Treatment Center in St. Peters, MO. Learn about our providers, treatment philosophy, and patient-first approach."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-brand-light py-24 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-brand-navy leading-tight mb-6">
        About Morning Star Neuropathy & Pain Treatment Center
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        We are dedicated to helping patients in St. Peters, MO and the greater St. Louis area find lasting relief from neuropathy and chronic pain through advanced, non-invasive care.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Clinic Story -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-6">Our Story</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Morning Star Neuropathy & Pain Treatment Center was founded to serve the people of St. Peters, St. Charles County, and the greater St. Louis metropolitan area who are living with neuropathy, chronic pain, and degenerative conditions. Too many patients in our community were told that their only options were long-term medication, repeated cortisone injections, or invasive surgery. We saw an opportunity to offer something better — a clinic built from the ground up around advanced, non-invasive treatments that address the actual source of pain rather than simply masking the symptoms.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        The clinic was born from a deep commitment to compassionate, evidence-based care. Our founders recognized that patients with peripheral neuropathy, joint degeneration, and chronic musculoskeletal pain deserve access to the same regenerative and neuromodulation technologies that were once limited to major academic medical centers. By bringing these treatments to a comfortable, patient-focused setting in St. Peters, we made it possible for people across the region to receive world-class care close to home.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg leading-relaxed">
        Since opening our doors, Morning Star has helped hundreds of patients regain sensation, reduce pain, improve mobility, and return to the activities they love. We measure our success not by the number of procedures we perform, but by the quality of life our patients reclaim.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Treatment Philosophy -->
  <section class="bg-brand-light py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-6">Our Treatment Philosophy</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        At Morning Star, every treatment decision starts with a single question: what is causing this patient's pain? We believe that lasting relief is only possible when the root cause of a condition is identified and addressed directly. That is why every new patient at our clinic receives a thorough evaluation — including a detailed health history review, neurological assessment, and diagnostic workup — before any treatment is recommended.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Our approach is patient-centered, non-invasive, and grounded in evidence-based medicine. We combine advanced technologies such as neuromodulation, platelet-rich plasma therapy, exosome-based regenerative therapy, and hyaluronic acid injections with individualized care plans tailored to each patient's unique condition, lifestyle, and goals. Rather than offering a one-size-fits-all protocol, we develop a customized roadmap for recovery that evolves as the patient progresses.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg leading-relaxed">
        We are committed to transparency at every step. Patients understand exactly what their treatment involves, why it was recommended, and what outcomes they can realistically expect. This collaborative approach builds trust and empowers patients to take an active role in their recovery journey.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Provider Credentials -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-6">Our Providers</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        The clinical team at Morning Star includes experienced medical professionals who specialize in neuropathy, pain management, and regenerative medicine. Our practitioners hold advanced training in neuromodulation techniques, platelet-rich plasma therapy, exosome therapy, hyaluronic acid joint injections, and medically supervised weight management. Each team member brings a deep understanding of the neuromuscular and musculoskeletal systems that allows us to diagnose and treat complex pain conditions with precision.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg leading-relaxed">
        Continuous education is a cornerstone of our practice. Our providers regularly attend national conferences, complete advanced certifications, and stay current with peer-reviewed research to ensure that every patient at Morning Star receives the most effective and up-to-date treatment options available. When new evidence supports a better approach, we adopt it — because our patients deserve nothing less than the best care modern medicine can offer.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Community Commitment -->
  <section class="bg-brand-light py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy text-center mb-6">Serving Our Community</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg leading-relaxed text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-12">
        Morning Star Neuropathy & Pain Treatment Center is proud to serve patients throughout St. Peters, St. Charles County, O'Fallon, Wentzville, Chesterfield, and surrounding communities across the greater St. Louis region. Our clinic is conveniently located at 4710 Mexico Rd, Suite C, near Mid Rivers Mall Drive, with easy access from Interstate 70 and Highway 94.
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
        {[
          'St. Peters', 'O\'Fallon', 'St. Charles', 'Wentzville',
          'Chesterfield', 'St. Louis', 'Florissant', 'Wildwood',
          'Ballwin', 'Kirkwood', 'Maryland Heights', 'University City',
        ].map((city) => (
          <div class="bg-white rounded-lg px-5 py-4 flex items-center gap-3 shadow-sm">
            <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-brand-blue flex-shrink-0"></span>
            <span class="text-brand-navy font-medium">{city}</span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-brand-navy text-white py-16 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Ready to Get Started?</h2>
      <p class="text-blue-200 mb-8">
        Schedule an appointment today and take the first step toward a pain-free life. Call us at <a href="tel:6362440124" class="underline hover:text-white">(636) 244-0124</a> or book online.
      </p>
      <a href="/schedule-appointment" class="px-8 py-3 bg-white text-brand-navy font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-50 transition-colors">
        Schedule Appointment
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
